				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$b_a(t)$$\end{document}ba(t) are both constant in this range. However, for the first half of 2020, things are less obvious. The variations observed in the magenta curve may result from reductions in \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
